# Almalyk, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Almalyk (; , AlmalÄ±q) is a rural locality (a village) in Buzovyazovsky Selsoviet, Karmaskalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 236 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Almalyk is located 33 km southwest of Karmaskaly (the district's administrative centre) by road. Buzovyazbash is the nearest rural locality.
